You will see that for 5-digit and above numbers, the Spanish formatter does indeed group the numbers as expected.

However, if you use a German formatter (`de-DE`), it correctly formats the 4-digit numeric.

Output:

    Spanish (ES)
    1234,56 €
    12.345,67 €
    123.456,78 €

    German (de-DE)
    1.234,56 €
    12.345,67 €
    123.456,78 €

